    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-10-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 10,
                            1893</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 61 of 19th ultimo and
                        the copy which you inclose of a letter from our consul at Sivas to our
                        consul-general at Constantinople, setting forth the unfriendly attitude and
                        acts of the vali of Sivas, in which province Marsovan is situate, toward
                        Americans there residing.</p>
                <p>The continuance and development of good will at Marsovan will largely depend,
                        as you point out, on the discretion and tact of the American officers of the
                        college, but their efforts to commend their enterprise as law-abiding and
                        beneficial to the community should not be neutralized by malevolent
                        misrepresentations and treatment such as is attributed, apparently of actual
                        knowledge, to the vali of Sivas.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
